The paper deals with the problem of segmenting medical images using deep neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach to compute a confidence map from extreme points, which is a machine learning technique, and uses a deep neural network to develop a class-agnostic segmentation model. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical images, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a deep neural network to develop the segmentation model, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
